-15 10:55:42',125),(306,12,'what is chemistry',NULL,'Chemistry is the study of matter and its properties as well as how matter changes. It\'s a vast and fascinating subject that explores the composition, structure, properties, and reactions of matter.  It\'s all around us, from the air we breathe to the food we eat! \n','2024-08-15 10:56:50',125),(307,12,'hey',NULL,'Hi there!  I\'m happy to help with any chemistry questions you have.  What are you working on today? 😊 \n','2024-08-15 10:57:29',126),(308,12,'what is chemistry',NULL,'Chemistry is the study of matter and its properties as well as how matter changes. It\'s a vast and fascinating subject that explores the building blocks of the universe, from the smallest atoms to the complex molecules that make up our bodies and everything around us.  \n\nThink of chemistry as the language we use to understand the world at a molecular level. We use it to explain things like:\n\n* **Why water is a liquid at room temperature:**  It\'s all about the bonds between hydrogen and oxygen atoms.\n* **How medicines work:**  Understanding the chemical reactions that occur in our bodies allows us to create drugs that target specific diseases.\n* **The composition of different materials:** From the plastic in your phone to the fabric of your clothes, chemistry tells us what these things are made of. \n\nIt\'s a subject that connects to many other areas of science, like biology, physics, and medicine.  \n\nDo you have any specific areas within chemistry you\'d like to explore?  😊 \n','2024-08-15 10:57:40',126),(313,17,'hey',NULL,'Hi there! 👋  What chemistry question can I help you with today? 😊 \n','2024-08-15 12:00:09',131),(314,18,'what is chemistry',NULL,'Chemistry is the study of matter and its properties as well as how matter changes. It\'s a fascinating subject that explores the composition, structure, properties, and reactions of matter. \n\nThink of it like this: \n* **Matter:** Everything around us, from the air we breathe to the water we drink, is made up of matter. \n* **Properties:** These are the characteristics that describe matter, like its color, smell, taste, density, and melting point. \n* **Changes:** Matter can undergo different transformations, like chemical reactions where new substances are formed. \n\nSo, in a nutshell, chemistry helps us understand the world around us at a fundamental level! \n','2024-08-15 12:01:25',132),(315,18,'hey',NULL,'Hello! How can I help you today? Perhaps you have a question about a particular chemical reaction or a concept you\'re struggling with.  😊 \n','2024-08-15 12:14:45',132),(316,18,'what is chemistry',NULL,'Chemistry is the study of matter and its properties as well as how matter changes. It\'s a vast and fascinating subject that explores the composition, structure, properties, and reactions of matter.  Think of it as the science that explains the world around us at a molecular level! \n','2024-08-15 12:15:19',132),(317,18,'what is science',NULL,'Science is a fascinating and ever-evolving field that seeks to understand the natural world through observation, experimentation, and analysis. It\'s a systematic way of exploring and explaining phenomena, leading to new discoveries and technologies that shape our world. \n\nThink of it as a journey of discovery, where we constantly question, investigate, and refine our understanding of how things work.  \n\nLet me know if you have any specific chemistry-related questions, I\'d be happy to help! \n','2024-08-15 12:19:47',133),(318,18,'can you tell me more in detail',NULL,'Kindly ask a chemistry-related question. Thank you. \n','2024-08-15 12:20:49',133),(319,18,'what is chemistry',NULL,'Chemistry is the study of matter and its properties as well as how matter changes. It\'s a fascinating subject that explores the composition, structure, properties, and reactions of substances. Think of it as the science that explains everything around you, from the air you breathe to the food you eat and the materials you use every day! \n','2024-08-15 12:21:48',133),(320,18,'tell me more',NULL,'That\'s a great question!  Let\'s dive a little deeper.  \n\nChemistry is all about understanding the building blocks of the universe. We explore atoms and how they combine to form molecules.  We look at how these molecules interact with each other to create the materials we see around us.  Think about the difference between water, which is a liquid, and ice, which is solid, even though they are made of the same components (hydrogen and oxygen).  Chemistry helps us understand why that happens!\n\nDo you have any particular areas of chemistry you\'d like to learn more about? For example, are you interested in the different types of chemical reactions, or perhaps the structure of atoms?  Let me know, and we can explore further! \n','2024-08-15 12:21:52',133),(321,18,'can you give me some examples',NULL,'Sure!  What kind of examples are you looking for?  Can you tell me a bit more about the topic you are interested in?  For example, are you looking for examples of chemical reactions, types of bonding, or something else entirely?  The more details you can provide, the better I can help you! \n','2024-08-15 12:22:04',133),(322,19,'some more info',NULL,'Please provide me with the question you have in mind. I\'d be happy to help you with it. It would be helpful if you could tell me what the topic is about and any specific parts you\'re struggling with.  \n','2024-08-15 12:22:41',134),(323,18,'some more info',NULL,'Please provide me with more information about what you\'d like to know. For instance, are you looking for examples of chemical reactions, types of bonding, or something else entirely? The more details you give, the better I can assist you! \n','2024-08-15 12:23:05',133),(324,12,'answer this','/uploads/eea946b39652c927adbb4aa00.51.29.png','Please provide me with the question you would like me to answer. I\'m happy to help! 😊 \n','2024-08-15 12:33:52',129),(325,12,'answer this','